# Plan: solar-system

## Goal
Make this subfolder compliant with the repo's CLAUDE.md while preserving the
hand-written 3D viewer (`index.html`) as the landing page on the deployed site.

## Current state
- `index.html` is a self-contained 3D solar system viewer.
- No `index.md`, so the folder was skipped by the previous build script.
- The previous build script would also have overwritten `index.html` if an
  `index.md` were added.

## Constraint
Per user instruction, the workflow must NEVER replace an existing `index.html`.

## Steps
1. Patch `.github/scripts/build_site.py` so that:
   - Subfolders with only `index.html` are still copied to `_site/`.
   - When both `index.md` and `index.html` exist, the hand-written
     `index.html` is kept untouched.
   - When only `index.md` exists, it is rendered to `index.html` as before.
2. Add a documentation-only `index.md` in this folder. It will not be
   rendered (because `index.html` exists) but satisfies the CLAUDE.md rule
   that every subfolder must contain an `index.md`. It also serves as the
   source-of-truth description of the experiment.

## Out of scope
- Modifying the 3D viewer itself.
- Splitting the viewer into a separate URL (e.g. `viewer.html`).

## Verification
- After push, the `pages.yml` run should succeed.
- `/solar-system/` on the deployed site should still serve the original
  3D viewer (byte-identical to the committed `index.html`).
